{
  "texts": [
    "Returning to the other discussed example.",
    "Police officer: \"I want to stop that car; I do not like the look of it. \"",
    "This noticeably short descriptive statement describes the operationalization of a hunch by the officer in question.",
    "They describe that they wish to act to stop the car because they do not \"like the look of it. \"",
    "This is open to interpretive bias from an onlooker who does not have the foundational sensory input of a police officer, and it is possible to read this statement in a negative or even punitive manner."
  ]
}